{{Infobox Individual Snooker Tournament |tournament_name=Australian Professional Championship |logo= |dates=August 1978 |venue= |location= |country=Australia |organisation=[[World Professional Billiards and Snooker Association|WPBSA]] |format=Non-[[Snooker world rankings|ranking]] event |Total prize fund= |winners_share= |highest_break= |winner={{flagicon|AUS}} [[Eddie Charlton]] |runner_up={{flagicon|AUS}} [[Ian Anderson (snooker player)|Ian Anderson]] |score=29–13 |previous=[[1977 Australian Professional Championship|1977]] |next=[[1984 Australian Professional Championship|1984]] }}
The '''1978 [[Australian Professional Championship]]''' was a professional non-[[Snooker world rankings|ranking]] snooker tournament, which took place in August 1978.<ref>{{citeweb|title=Other National Professional Championships|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120107161810/http://www.cajt.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/natpro.html|publisher=Chris Turner's Snooker Archive|accessdate=22 February 2018}}</ref>
[[Eddie Charlton]] won the tournament defeating [[Ian Anderson (snooker player)|Ian Anderson]] 29–13 in the final.<ref name="Snooker Database">{{citeweb|title=1978 Australian Professional Championship Results Grid|url=http://www.snookerdatabase.co.uk/EventResultGrid.aspx?EventKey=612|publisher=Snooker Database|accessdate=22 February 2018}}</ref>
