{{Infobox Organization |name = Renju International Federation |image = |size = |type = [[International organization]] |motto = |formation = {{start date and age|1988|8|8}} |headquarters = [[Stockholm]], [[Sweden]] |membership = 20 members |leader_title = President |leader_name = Anders Henningsson |language = |website = [http://renju.net renju.net] }}
The Renju International Federation (RIF) is an international organization which was founded in [[Stockholm]], [[Sweden]] in August 8, 1988. The main purpose of the federation is to unit all the [[Renju]] and [[gomoku]] national federations all over the world, organize international tournaments such as [[World Championships in Renju|World Championships]], together with other activities in renju and gomoku, and spread renju activities in the world. The federation carry out the General Assembly every two years.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://www.renju.net/organizations/rif.php|title=The Renju International Federation|last=|first=|date=|website=Renju.Net|publisher=|access-date=2017-01-20}}</ref><ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=http://renju.net/organizations/RIF%20Statutes%202017-10-25.pdf|title=The Statutes of The Renju International Federation|last=|first=|date=2017-10-25|website=Renju International Federation|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2018-10-19}}</ref>
== The Central Committee == The Central Committee is responsible to the current status of the Renju International Federation, together with the activities of the officials of the Federation.<ref name=":0" /> According to the status, there are 6 positions in the Central Committee.<ref name=":1" /> {| class="wikitable" |+ !Position !Name !Country |- |President |Anders Henningsson |{{flag|Sweden}} |- |Vice President |[[Norihiko Kawamura]] |{{Flag|Japan}} |- |Vice President |Dmitry Epifanov |{{Flag|Russia}} |- |General Secretary |[[Ants Soosõrv]] |{{Flag|Estonia}} |- |Treasurer |Stefan Karlsson |{{Flag|Sweden}} |- |PR Manager |Ilya Katsev |{{Flag|Russia}} |}
==Members== The Renju International Federation was founded in 1988 by 3 founder members: [[Japan]], [[Soviet Union]] and [[Sweden]]. Up to 2017, there have been 20 members in the Renju International Federation. The list of members follows.<ref name=":0" /> {| class="wikitable" |- !Member !Year of joining !Status |- |{{flag|Japan}} |1988 |Founder Member |- |{{flag|Russia}} |1988 |Founder Member{{efn|Russia has inherited the place of the Soviet Union since 1992.|group=m}} |- |{{flag|Sweden}} |1988 |Founder Member |- |{{flag|Canada}} |2003 |Member |- |{{flag|China}} |1996 |Member |- |{{flag|Macau, China}} |2015 |Member |- |{{flag|Chinese Taipei}} |1999 |Member |- |{{flag|Czech Republic}} |2003 |Member |- |{{flag|Estonia}} |1988 |Member |- |{{flag|Finland}} |2003 |Member |- |{{flag|Greece}} |2016 |Member |- |{{flag|South Korea}} |2001 |Member |- |{{flag|Poland}} |2009 |Member |- |{{flag|Turkey}} |2015 |Member |- |{{flag|Uzbekistan}} |1999 |Member |- |{{flag|Armenia}} |1988 |Idle |- |{{flag|Azerbaijan}} |1988 |Idle |- |{{flag|Belarus}} |1988 |Idle |- |{{flag|Latvia}} |1988 |Idle |- |{{flag|Ukraine}} |1988 |Idle |}
